        p.prod-info__top-txt This description outlines the basic components that make up the structure of a sofa, emphasizing its frame, upholstery, cushions, and legs.
        p.prod-info__txt A sofa, also known as a couch or settee, is a staple piece of furniture found in homes, offices, and public spaces worldwide. It typically consists of a frame with cushions that provide seating for two or more people. Sofas vary widely in design, material, size, and functionality, catering to diverse aesthetic preferences and practical needs.
